'''Consumer value''' is used to describe a [[consumer|consumer's]] strong relative preference for certain [[Subjectivity|subjectively]] evaluated product or service attribute.<ref>Holbrook, Morris B. Consumer value: a framework for analysis and research. Psychology Press, 1999.</ref><ref>Sánchez-Fernández, Raquel, M. Angeles Iniesta-Bonillo, and Morris B. Holbrook. "The conceptualisation and measurement of consumer value in services." International Journal of Market Research 51, no. 1 (2009): 93-113.</ref><ref>Holbrook, Morris B. "Special session summary customer value C a framework for analysis and research." NA-Advances in Consumer Research Volume 23 (1996).</ref><ref>Thompson, Craig J., and Maura Troester. "Consumer value systems in the age of postmodern fragmentation: The case of the natural health microculture." Journal of consumer research 28, no. 4 (2002): 550-571.</ref> These values include efficiency, excellence, status, esteem, play, aesthetics, [[ethics]] and [[spirituality]].
