{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians --> | name = Jason Lyle Black | image = Jason Lyle Black (40449754724).jpg | caption = Jason Lyle Black in 2018 | background = non_vocal_instrumentalist | birth_name = Jason Lyle Black | birth_date = | death_date = | instrument = [[Piano]] | genre = Classical, New Age | occupation = Pianist, composer | years_active = 2010–present | label = [[Stone Angel Music]] | website = {{URL|http://www.jasonlyleblack.com/}} }}
'''Jason Lyle Black''' is an American pianist, composer, and Billboard-charting artist.
==Biography== Black grew up in [[Livermore, California]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jasonlyleblack.com/for-fans/ |title=Frequently Asked Questions |website=JasonLyleBlack.com |accessdate=April 9, 2018}}</ref> He participated in the final round of the [[73rd Scripps National Spelling Bee]] in 2000.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/can-you-spell-winner/ |title=Can You Spell 'Winner?' |publisher=CBS News |accessdate=April 9, 2018}}</ref> Black started learning how to play the piano at age 8, and started playing it backwards at age 14. He went to college at [[Brigham Young University]], where he played at concerts and studied accounting.<ref>{{cite web |last=Corpus |first=Eric |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/this-guy-plays-the-piano-backwards-and-blows-your-mind-video-111936/ |title=This Guy Plays the Piano Backwards and Blows Your Mind (VIDEO) |work=Christian Post |date=January 2, 2014 |accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref> After graduating in 2012, he became a [[Certified Public Accountant]], but then decided to focus his career on becoming a touring musician.<ref name="heraldextra">{{cite web |last=Harris |first=Sarah |url=https://www.heraldextra.com/entertainment/music/pianist-jason-lyle-black-to-turn-around-expectations-in-scera/article_142c441f-5b73-59d0-a255-db2a280c42b6.html |title=Pianist Jason Lyle Black to turn around expectations in SCERA shows |work=Daily Herald |date=February 8, 2018 |accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref>
==Discography== In 2016, Black signed to [[Stone Angel Music]], releasing album ''Piano Preludes'' in May, from producer [[Paul Cardall]].<ref name="mainlypiano.com">{{cite web |last=Parsons |first=Kathy |url=http://mainlypiano.com/reviews/jason-lyle-black-piano-preludes |title=Album Review: Piano Preludes |work=Mainly Piano |date=May 9, 2016 |accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref> The album featured the violinist [[Jenny Oaks Baker]] as a guest soloist.<ref name="fox13now.com">{{cite news |last=Graham |first=Brittany |url=http://fox13now.com/2016/05/04/youtube-piano-star-jason-lyle-black-debuts-his-new-album/ |title=Youtube piano star Jason Lyle Black debuts his new album |date=May 4, 2016 |work=Fox 13 Salt Lake City |accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref> ''Piano Preludes'' debuted at #2 on the Billboard New Age chart,<ref name="deseretnews.com">{{cite news |last=Cobb |first=Sydney |url=https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865654722/Pianist-Jason-Lyle-Blacks-debut-Piano-Preludes-album-hits-No-2-on-Billboard-New-Age-chart.html |title=Pianist Jason Lyle Black's debut 'Piano Preludes' album hits No. 2 on Billboard New Age chart |date=May 21, 2016 |work=Deseret News |accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref> spending three weeks in the #2 spot.<ref name="billboard.com">{{cite web|url= http://www.billboard.com/charts/new-age-albums/2016-06-11 |title=New Age Music: Top New Age Albums Chart |date=June 11, 2016 |work=Billboard}}</ref> Music critic Kathy Parsons called the album "masterful",<ref name="mainlypiano.com"/> and ''Deseret News'' reporter Sydney Cobb called it "peaceful."<ref name="deseretnews.com"/>
Black is also known for his viral videos based on songs from the movies ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]'' and ''[[Up (2009 film)|Up]]''.<ref name="kutv.com">{{cite news |url=http://kutv.com/features/the-refresh/the-refresh-jason-lyle-black-to-perform-in-sandy-july-6th |title=The Refresh: Jason Lyle Black 'Backwards Piano Man' to perform free concert in Sandy |publisher=KUTV |date=July 5, 2016 |accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref> and for his performance on [[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]].<ref name="deseretnews.com2">{{cite web|url= http://www.deseretnews.com/article/865653710/Watch-live-Pianist-Jason-Lyle-Black-performs-songs-from-new-album-at-Deseret-Book.html?pg=all |title=Watch live: Pianist Jason Lyle Black performs songs from new album at Deseret Book |work=Deseret News |date=May 6, 2016 |accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref> Black has previously won the Utah Music Awards.<ref name="good4utah.com">{{cite news |last=DeGering |first=Nicea |url=http://www.good4utah.com/news/midday/utah-music-awards-recognize-the-best-musicians-in-the-world |title=Utah Music Awards Recognize the Best Musicians in the World |work=Good4Utah |date=July 11, 2016 |accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== Black is a member of [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]].<ref name="heraldextra"/> He resides in [[Salt Lake City]], Utah.<ref>{{cite news |last=Borresen |first=Kelsey |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/grandparents-play-up-themed-duet_us_5627e0f3e4b0bce34703b225 |title=Grandma And Grandpa Celebrate 60+ Years Of Marriage With 'Up'-Themed Duet |date=October 21, 2015 |work=HuffPost |accessdate=April 9, 2018}}</ref>
